Kingswood College Grade 12 pupil Bradley Moorcroft is looking to put his feet up for a few days after his eight distinctions landed him a spot on the Independent Examinations Board s outstanding and commendable achievements list.All IEB matriculants can check their exam results live at matric.sowetanlive.co.za The pressure is off now. I am really happy with my results he said. I am just looking forward to enjoying what s left of the holidays with my friends. Among the distinctions the school s headboy achieved were 99% for mathematics and 95% for advanced programme maths.His other distinctions came from accounting Afrikaans English information technology physical science and life orientation.Read the full story on HeraldLIVE: Calling all matrics: claim your fame and you could win R6,000- TMG Digital/The Herald 